    Class SHAKE256 implements the SHAKE-256 extensible output hash function with a 64-byte (512-bit) message. The SHAKE-256 cryptographic function's input A is the first portion of the message (256 bits); input B is the second portion of the message (256 bits); output C is the digest (fixed at 2048 bits).
